article.description: Kobe Bryant fed Smush Parker for a game-tying layup with 0.1 seconds left and helped the Los Angeles Lakers go on to a 132-128 OT win.
article.headline: Bryant carries Lakers to comeback OT win over Kings
article.linkText: Kobe scores 42 to power Lakers' OT victory
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- In a Jan. 4 story about the NBA game between the Los Angeles Lakers and Sacramento Kings, The Associated Press misreported the Lakers' player who hit a 3-pointer with 4.7 seconds to go in regulation. The player was Vladimir Radmanovich, not Sasha Vujacic.
